# Company: Acme AI

## Identity
- **One-liner:** AI-powered contract review for mid-market legal teams
- **Founded:** August 2025
- **Stage:** Seed ($1.2M raised)
- **Legal entity:** Acme AI, Inc. (Delaware C-Corp)

## Business Model
- B2B SaaS, usage-based pricing ($0.10/contract reviewed)
- Monthly subscription tier at $499/mo (unlimited reviews, up to 5 seats)
- Target ACV: $6,000

## Target Market
- Primary: In-house legal ops teams at companies 50–500 employees
- Secondary: Boutique law firms (10–50 lawyers)
- Geography: US-first, English contracts only

## Current Product Status
- Private beta: 12 design partners
- Core features: contract upload, clause extraction, risk flagging
- Not yet: redlining, negotiation suggestions, multi-party workflows

## Top 3 Strategic Priorities (Q2 2026)
1. Convert 10 design partners to paid customers
2. Reduce time-to-first-value from 3 days to 30 minutes
3. Close Series A ($5M) by Q3 2026

## Key Metrics (as of 2026-04-06)
- ARR: $0 (pre-revenue, design partner phase)
- Pipeline: 4 paid conversations active
- NPS: Not yet measured
- Churn: N/A
